Nigerian singer and songwriter Mr Eazi has sent an apology to his Kenyan fans after his flight was canceled over technical issues. He was expected to be in Kenya yesterday for a one-day media tour to promote his new song, Property. Speaking to Kiss 100 on the phone, Eazi said,Â "I want to really apologise to my Kenyan fans because I am not able to come. My flight got canceled and we had to get down due to technical issues. "However, I will plan again and come to Kenya because I love you guys so much. I just dropped a new song called 'Property', which I want you to enjoy as much as possible. "Thank you so much for your continued support."